4:
Oh... Hello. You've come to visit us
again?
7:
Yeah, haha... Sorry to bother you,
but... We were wondering if you
could extend our underwater
breathing again...
10:
The illegal dumping just won't stop...
How are we supposed to get along
with folk like that around?
17:
Just sit back and relax, because this
marine bunny princess is about to
save the day!
21:
But... How should we go about
finding illegal dumpers?
26:
Just leave that to me! I'll hatch the
perfect plan to crack this case wide
open.
32:
Thanks for bringing out such a nice
ship, Mister!
35:
Ahaha! Just say the word, and I'll
buy a whole fleet for you!
36:
We're approaching the area where
the suspicious ship was spotted.
Everyone ready?
39:
All righty, then. If this shipping
industry guy and my contact in the
navy are correct, this should be the
place...
48:
That's what I like to hear! Thanks,
you guys!
53: Yeah, right! She was looking at me!
55:
You got barnacles in yer eyes? I be
the one she was looking at!
58:
Hey, no fighting! I want to see your
big, bright smiles!
62:
The power of friendship is what's
gonna make us win today!
66:
I knew she had faith in her contacts,
but I never imagined she could
amass such numbers in a single
day...
78:
That's the ship we've been looking
for, no doubt!
82: Faroa, get the ship in range!
87:
If we get any closer, they'll just run
away. We've gotta take that option
away from them, first!
101:
Captain! We're taking fire from a
b-battleship!
103:
Curses! Military vessels can't be firin'
without warning!
114:
Dumping garbage in the ocean's
illegal, you guys! You're making the
water all icky and causing trouble
for everyone.
117:
Hmph... Why should we care about
other folk? We're barely surviving as
it is.
118:
...Me right arm's been no good since
the accident. How would I make an
honest living?
119:
We got no education or
connections. This is all we can do to
get by!
121:
Society leaves some folk without
options. You understand that much,
I'm sure.
122: I'm giving me crew a chance at life!
125:
Do you think we could give these
guys work patrolling the waters?
Instead of throwing them behind
bars.
128:
What?! We can't accept people like
this into our ranks!
131:
If something bad happens, I'll take
responsibility for it.
133:
We already know they're a capable
bunch... So would you please do this,
just for me?
136:
...W-well... If you put it like that, I
guess I have no choice.
139:
It's decided, then. You
trash-dumpers are gonna be
patrolling the waters as upstanding
members of society, now!
142:
You got sea pickles for brains, girlie?
You can't just decide this for us!
145:
Hey, that's rude... Though I won't
deny that I don't always think things
through.
147:
But how's it look from your point of
view? If you want a place to fit in, I'm
ready to give you one.
150:
You'll even be appreciated for the
work you do for once!
153:
...Not like we got much of a choice.
We'll be hanged if we refuse.
154:
Hmph! Fine, we'll do it! We'll be...
h-honest folk...
157:
First things first, you've got a lot of
cleaning up to do! You're the ones
responsible for the mess, after all.
162:
It's just as you said, Alk. She's a hero
indeed.
